      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Can we get some amount of reporting as to how good as a PUF that SRAM behaves?\nLike, reading the power-on bit pattern of a few dies and seeing how stable and unique it is per-die?\n\nIf it's at least not-terrible, I could try next week about getting a probably-smallest-tested SRAM macro set up, if I can think of a way to read it _at all_ without an electrical pad contact to the die.",
